        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:7:3:56:2",
        "text": [
          " سَمِعْتُ أَبَا عَبْدِ اللَّهِ ( عليه السلام ) يَقُولُ لَا حَدَّ لِمَنْ لَا حَدَّ عَلَيْهِ يَعْنِي لَوْ أَنَّ مَجْنُوناً قَذَفَ رَجُلًا لَمْ أَرَ عَلَيْهِ شَيْئاً وَ لَوْ قَذَفَهُ رَجُلٌ فَقَالَ لَهُ يَا زَانِ لَمْ يَكُنْ عَلَيْهِ حَدٌّ ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "Ibn Mahboub, from Abu Ayoub, from Fuzeyl Bin Yasaar who said, ",
            "‘I heard Abu Abdullah<sup>asws</sup> saying: ‘There is no Penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>) for the one upon whom there is no Penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>), meaning, if an insane person were to slander a man, I<sup>asws</sup> do not see anything upon him, and if a man were to slander him, so he says to him, ‘O adulterer’, there would be no Penalty (<span class=\"iTxt\">Hadd</span>) upon him (either)’."
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
